node.text:
Sending love to all my fellow minorities out there who are trying to make their way but it requires doing approx 836 panels. NO MORE PANELS BRUH 😫 (unless you got a budget… 👀) 

Real talk, I’m so happy to see the progress happening in Hollywood and other industries. It’s no doubt that things are improving. But it’s also no doubt that many corporations out there are being inclusive in really shallow ways. Inclusion isn’t about checking off boxes or giving people the bare minimum; it’s about understanding that diverse voices represent the world we live in and add valuable perspective. It’s about supporting ideas and voices beyond just letting them in a room. Diversity isn’t one spot to fill on your roster so you can pat yourself on the back. It’s truly the way things always should have been. But we’ll get there 💪🏽❤️

Because female nipples are too sexy whereas male nipples are casual! Duh?! I know the world is literally burning and sick but the censoring of female bodies should definitely still remain a top priority… 👀🧐

Okay real talk, the most difficult part of making this video was trying to make commentary about these stupid rules while also staying within the rules so my video wouldn’t get taken down. Honestly it still might get taken down. Enjoy it while you can! 

Also, I got mad love for IG and I know this issue is greater than just this platform. In fact most platforms have these crazy rules around the female body. One Dominatrix told me that her business accounts kept getting flagged so to prevent that, she changed her profile settings to MALE and they stopped getting taking down. This is about corporations and masses and what they deem is appropriate. Because should some boobies be allowed on here one day, I’m sure one million people will be pressed about it. And I really gotta ask, why? After you got breastfed, did that nipple turn into a tiny dangerous assassin? 

Shout outs to boss women out there not giving an eff like @mileycyrus @badgalriri @chrissyteigen and @chelseahandler. I’m not at your level yet but l I aspire to be. Right now I’m still trying to work up the courage to not wear a bra or nipple covers when it’s cold outside 😂

Let’s start seeing real life... 
•••
I love the original by @theweeknd so much, I was inspired to create a version about social media/phone addiction. It’s something I really struggle with, especially having a job that is so deeply intertwined with digital lust. A little reminder to see real life. 

It pained me to reframe this project for IG because the full frame video is such a visual treat. Link in bio to watch it, in all its glory on YouTube. Shoutouts to my DP @cldorson who nailed my vision and brought such cinematic brilliance to the project. 

Shoutouts to @durranibros for the incredible recreation of the song. Usually it’s mentally straining to listen to a song 100 times while shooting but this one was a treat. 

Thank you to the entire crew for working hard on this beast of a concept that took three shoot days, one of which was overnight. Shoutouts @friedpotayters for always reassuring everyone that “Lilly’s insanely ambitious ideas are somehow possible,” because we always find a way. 

I’m really proud of this one. In some ways, it communicates something I can’t with just words. Turning pain into art. I hope you enjoy it ❤️

#BlindingLikes

Based 100% on a true story 😂💀 real talk, we’ve made a lot of progress in this industry in terms of diversity but there’s still a long way to go because the same group of powerful people run the show behind the scenes. This sketch is dedicated to anyone who has ever been in a room, pitching an idea about their experience, only to have no one else understand it. (Me. This video is dedicated to me.) Here’s to more diversity on the screen but also behind the camera and in the business. 

Also, I wanna say that these other actors became my homies in like four seconds. I legit had a blast with them and also kind of... turned into them? LOL. A hoot. #LateWithLilly

node.text:
Sending love to all my fellow minorities out there who are trying to make their way but it requires doing approx 836 panels. NO MORE PANELS BRUH 😫 (unless you got a budget… 👀) 

Real talk, I’m so happy to see the progress happening in Hollywood and other industries. It’s no doubt that things are improving. But it’s also no doubt that many corporations out there are being inclusive in really shallow ways. Inclusion isn’t about checking off boxes or giving people the bare minimum; it’s about understanding that diverse voices represent the world we live in and add valuable perspective. It’s about supporting ideas and voices beyond just letting them in a room. Diversity isn’t one spot to fill on your roster so you can pat yourself on the back. It’s truly the way things always should have been. But we’ll get there 💪🏽❤️

Forget the Super Bowl. The most intense sport I know is paying the bill at a brown restaurant. 👀😂 As a kid I learned all my street smarts from the negotiations and tactics I saw go down in Indian Restaurants. And you know what, I’m a better human because of it!! One time
I called ahead and gave them my credit card info… my uncle was furious LOL

I lowkey wish I worked at a desi spot though because I would eat all the gulab jamans. Ohhhh and kheer. Frig. I would dip the gulab jaman in kheer. EFF ME. I’m hungry. 😫😫
